<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,151,586]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,525,549]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
Feminine diminutive of the Greek 
<emphasis box="[744,838,526,549]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">eremites</emphasis>
, “dweller of the desert”, after the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1435,526,550]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
locality; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
